==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Storax
<hw>Sto"rax</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L. <ets>storax</ets>,
<ets>styrax</ets>, Gr. <?/. Cf. <er>Styrax</er>.]</ety> <def>Any one of
a number of similar complex resins obtained from the bark of several
trees and shrubs of the Styrax family. The most common of these is
<stype>liquid storax</stype>, a brown or gray semifluid substance of an
agreeable aromatic odor and balsamic taste, sometimes used in perfumery,
and in medicine as an expectorant.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A yellow aromatic honeylike substance, resembling, and
often confounded with, storax, is obtained from the American sweet gum
tree (<spn>Liquidambar styraciflua</spn>), and is much used as a chewing
gum, called <xex>sweet gum</xex>, and <xex>liquid storax</xex>. Cf.
<er>Liquidambar</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Store</ent>⟦br⟧
